            "id": "docx_1",
            "text": "Books also connect us with history and culture. They tell stories of people, places, and events that shaped the world. By reading, we learn from the experiences of others without living them ourselves.\n\nAnother benefit is that reading improves patience and concentration. Unlike short videos or quick posts, a book requires time and attention. This helps train our brain to focus for longer periods."
